                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="88809" author="pjones" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 11:19:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88775" author="fzago" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2014 21:16:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m running it from Ubuntu. I installed the PPA  then coccinelle (&lt;a href=&quot;http://coccinelle.lip6.fr/download.php&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://coccinelle.lip6.fr/download.php&lt;/a&gt;). It&apos;s the latest version (1.0.0-rc21).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I then run it from a linux kernel tree:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;make coccicheck -j7 M=&amp;lt;path to lustre&amp;gt;/lustre-release
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="88772" author="jhammond" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2014 21:06:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Frank,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m curious. Which version of coccinelle are you using? I used it some it a while ago but had too many issues with it. How well do you find it to work? Perhaps I should try it again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88709" author="fzago" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2014 15:43:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lustre/include/obd_support.h:792:19-22 is a false positive.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
